enterasysR2MgmtMIB.name: enterasysR2MgmtMIB

revisions.description: Added an object to support the management VLAN.
Imported etsysModules from the correct MIB and corrected range for INTEGER.
The initial version of this MIB module

enterasysR2MgmtMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
enterasysR2MgmtMIB.description: The Enterasys Networks Proprietary MIB module for entities implementing objects specific to the RoamAbout R2 Wireless Access Platform.

etsysR2MgmtMemorySize.name: etsysR2MgmtMemorySize
etsysR2MgmtMemorySize.description: The size of the memory in the Access Point in Mbytes.

etsysR2MgmtWEBInterface.name: etsysR2MgmtWEBInterface
etsysR2MgmtWEBInterface.description: Determines whether or not WEB Management is enabled or disabled.

etsysR2MgmtTelnetInterface.name: etsysR2MgmtTelnetInterface
etsysR2MgmtTelnetInterface.description: Determines whether or not Telnet Management is enabled or disabled.

etsysR2MgmtVlan.name: etsysR2MgmtVlan
etsysR2MgmtVlan.description: When non-zero this object specifies the management VLAN. This is the VLAN that remote management entities must use to communicate with this switch. Zero is a special value that specifies the default behavior, e.g., management on VLAN 1.

etsysR2MgmtPowerups.name: etsysR2MgmtPowerups
etsysR2MgmtPowerups.description: PERSISTENT: The number of times this device was powered on. Power Ups, Management Resets and Unsolicited Resets are all mutually exclusive.

etsysR2MgmtResets.name: etsysR2MgmtResets
etsysR2MgmtResets.description: PERSISTENT: Number of times the device was initialized with a management command. Power Ups, Management Resets and Unsolicited Resets are all mutually exclusive.

etsysR2MgmtUnsolicitedResets.name: etsysR2MgmtUnsolicitedResets
etsysR2MgmtUnsolicitedResets.description: PERSISTENT: Number of times the device initialized itself after encountering a fatal error. Power Ups, Management Resets & Unsolicited Resets are all mutually exclusive.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogNumEntries.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogNumEntries
etsysR2MgmtErrLogNumEntries.description: PERSISTENT: The number of entries in the etsysR2MgmtErrLogTable. The value of this object is initially zero. It is incremented as etsysR2MgmtErrLogEntries are added, to a maximum value. The maximum value is implementation specific.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogTable.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogTable
etsysR2MgmtErrLogTable.description: A table which describes errors encountered by the system.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogEntry.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogEntry
etsysR2MgmtErrLogEntry.description: A list of errors logged by the system.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogIndex.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogIndex
etsysR2MgmtErrLogIndex.description: PERSISTENT: The value of this object uniquely identifies an entry in the etsysR2MgmtErrLogTable.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogTimeStamp.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogTimeStamp
etsysR2MgmtErrLogTimeStamp.description: PERSISTENT: The value of sysUpTime at the time in which the error is logged.

etsysR2MgmtErrLogResetNumber.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogResetNumber
etsysR2MgmtErrLogResetNumber.description: PERSISTENT: The number of resets which have occurred at the time in which the error is logged. (This is the sum of etsysR2MgmtPowerups, etsysR2MgmtMgmtResets, and etsysR2MgmtUnsolicitedResets.)

etsysR2MgmtErrLogInfo.name: etsysR2MgmtErrLogInfo
etsysR2MgmtErrLogInfo.description: PERSISTENT: A textual description of the error being logged.

etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadUseBootp.name: etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadUseBootp
etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadUseBootp.description: DURABLE: Controls where the AccessPoint gets the information that it needs to upload crash dumps. When true(1), indicates that the AP should use the BootP protocol to auto-configure parameters such as its own IP address, gateway IP, subnet, TFTP server IP address, and directory name. When false(2), indicates that the AccessPoint should use locally-configured parameters stored in NVRAM.

etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadServerIP.name: etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadServerIP
etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadServerIP.description: DURABLE: The IP address of the TFTP server that should be used for crash dump uploads. This value will be ignored when 'etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadUseBootp' is 'false(2)'.

etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadDirectory.name: etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadDirectory
etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadDirectory.description: DURABLE: The name of the remote directory to which all crash dumps should be uploaded. This value will be ignored when 'etsysR2MgmtCrashUploadUseBootp' is 'false(2)'.

etsysR2MgmtUplineDumpMode.name: etsysR2MgmtUplineDumpMode
etsysR2MgmtUplineDumpMode.description: Determines whether or not a dump file is created on an Access Point crash.

etsysR2MgmtCompliance.name: etsysR2MgmtCompliance
etsysR2MgmtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that support Extended Switch.

etsysR2MgmtComplianceV2.name: etsysR2MgmtComplianceV2
etsysR2MgmtComplianceV2.description: The compliance statement for devices that support Extended Switch.
